@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes a device pool given the pool ARN. Does not allow deletion of curated pools owned by the system.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes a profile that can be applied to one or more private device instances.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes a network profile.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes an AWS Device Farm project, given the project ARN.  Deleting this resource does not stop an in-progress run.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes a completed remote access session and its results.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes the run, given the run ARN.  Deleting this resource does not stop an in-progress run.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes a Selenium testing project and all content generated under it.   You cannot undo this operation.   You cannot delete a project if it has active sessions.
@required {projectArn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes an upload given the upload ARN.
@required {arn: str}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Deletes a configuration for your Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) endpoint.
@required {arn: str}

