@endpoint POST /
@desc Gets information about unique problems, such as exceptions or crashes. Unique problems are defined as a single instance of an error across a run, job, or suite. For example, if a call in your application consistently raises an exception (OutOfBoundsException in MyActivity.java:386), ListUniqueProblems returns a single entry instead of many individual entries for that exception.
@required {arn: str}
@optional {nextToken: str}
@returns(200) {uniqueProblems: map<str,[UniqueProblem]>?, nextToken: str?}

